PINGNOTE

This program sends a little "update" to a (possibly remote) PINGSTAT program.

Synopsis:

$ pingnote <hostname> [-d <dialer>] [-s <svc>] [-t <datespec>] [-c <count>]
	[-lf <logfile>] [-Q] [-D] [-V]

where:

<hostname>	host to signal
-d <dialer>	dialer
-s <svc>	service
-t <datespec>	date to signal
-c <count>	count to add (default 1)
-lf <logfile>	log-file
-h <host>	hostname to update
-Q		quiet
-D		debug
-V		print program version to standard-error and then exit

